Package com.rb.nonbiz.collections

Class IidMap<V>

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.collections.HasLongMap<InstrumentId,​V>
com.rb.nonbiz.collections.IidMap<V>
All Implemented Interfaces:
PrintsInstruments
public class IidMap<V>
extends HasLongMap<InstrumentId,​V>
implements PrintsInstruments
A specialized map for the cases where the key is an InstrumentId.

It uses GNU Trove specialized maps for improved performance vs. RBMap, which is more general.

Note that this is not exactly like an RBMap, and has somewhat unorthodox ways to iterate over it (unlike RBMap, which sort of looks like a Map).

See Also:
HasLongMap

    • copyWithPresentInstrumentIdsRemoved

      public IidMap<V> copyWithPresentInstrumentIdsRemoved​(IidSet presentKeysToRemove)
      This does NOT modify this RBMap! It creates a copy, but with some keys removed. However, if toRemove is empty, we return the same IidMap as a performance optimization. Since IidMap is immutable, that's fine to do. Throws if one of the presentKeysToRemove is not in the map. ('present' here means 'assume it's present').

    • copyWithPossiblyAbsentInstrumentIdsRemoved

      public IidMap<V> copyWithPossiblyAbsentInstrumentIdsRemoved​(IidSet presentKeysToRemove)
      This does NOT modify this RBMap! It creates a copy, but with some keys removed. However, if toRemove is empty, we return the same IidMap as a performance optimization. Since IidMap is immutable, that's fine to do. Does not throw if one of the keysToRemove is not in the map.
